  "body": "relates to this MVP #11395\r\n\r\n**issue with this MVP above**\r\nit targets any user that doesn't have a keycard, without taking into account if the user has some value to protect or not\r\nin particular the banner is thus shown to every single one of new status users that use a standard (non keycard account).\r\nWe want the upsell to be more tageted \r\n\r\n**solution** \r\n- when a user has on his device, on one of the multiacounts, more than x (treshold to define) $ of value in eth or erc20 tokens (NFTs not considered since valuation is hard to get), on all his account that he controls from the seed of his multiaccount (read only accounts not considered, imported accounts with a sigle private key not taken into account)\r\n- then this user is being pushed a notification to let him aware that he can upgrade his security with a keycard\r\n- this notification is being sent not exactly when the treshold is passed but when it is passed and a given action is perfomed by the user. This action needs to be defined\r\n",
